go_data.justification: STUB1 is described as an E3 ubiquitin ligase.
STUB1 causes destabilization of PD-L1, either by direct modification of one of the lysines in the PD-L1 cytoplasmic domain or indirectly.

go_data.term: negative regulation of regulatory T cell differentiation
go_data.justification: The ubiquitin ligase Stub1 negatively modulates regulatory T cell suppressive activity by promoting degradation of the transcription factor Foxp3.
